Citation.sTitle: Isobaric Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium for the Binary Systems of Sec-butyl Acetate and Ethanol, 1-Propanol, or 2-Propanol at 101.3 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: The vapor liquid equilibrium (VLE) data of the ethanol + sec-butyl acetate, 1-propanol + sec-butyl acetate and 2-propanol + sec-butyl acetate mixtures were determined at 101.3 kPa. The first principle quantum chemistry calculation method, which focuses on the H-bond and interaction energies, is used to give insight into interactions at the molecular level. The experimental VLE data passed the thermodynamic consistency test. The data were regressed using Wilson, non-random two liquids and universal quasi-chemical equations. The 1-propanol + sec-butyl acetate mixture forms minimum temperature azeotropic mixture. The azeotropic temperature is 370.01 K and the composition of 1-propanol is 89.2 mole% when calculated with the Wilson model.
